                        <p>"It's social engineering", said junior Dave Mlaver, who is a smoker. "Smokers have an extra bad image and legislators are making it worse. Besides, it is outside the bounds of the government power. They're even encouraging taxes on cigarettes so that the government can pay for things." </p>
<p>Vice President for Student Affairs Larry Moneta said because the bill is still working its way through the legislative process and is not yet signed into law, he cannot yet comment on the issue. He added that when the bill becomes law, Duke will respond accordingly.</p>
